The All Progressives Congress (APC) has announced the date and time to officially unveil Senator Kashim Shettima as the party’s vice presidential candidate for the 2023 election. The APC in a statement released on Tuesday noted that Shettima will be unveiled on Wednesday, 20th July by 11 am at the Shehu Musa Yar’Adua Centre, Abuja. The statement reads, “The APC will formally unveil its Vice Presidential Candidate, Sen. Kashim Shettima to the Nigerian public on:Date:​ Wednesday, 20 July, 2022Venue:​ Shehu Musa Yar’Adua Centre, AbujaTime: 11am Prompt. The unveiling automatically means the APC will be fielding a Muslim-Muslim ticket for the 2023 presidential election.